<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="marketing">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta name="description" content="Very Good AdBlock is a fast, private ad blocker for Chrome, Firefox, and Safari on Mac, iPhone, and iPad. No account, telemetry, or bloat.">
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#100a0b">
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://verygoodadblock.org/">
    <script>
      // Set the theme before first paint (no flash): saved choice, else system.
      (function () {
        try {
          var saved = localStorage.getItem('vga-theme')
          var theme = saved || (matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: light)').matches ? 'light' : 'dark')
          document.documentElement.dataset.theme = theme
        }
        catch (e) {}
      })()
    </script>
    <meta property="og:type" content="website">
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="Very Good AdBlock">
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://verygoodadblock.org/">
    <meta property="og:title" content="Very Good AdBlock — fast, private ad blocking everywhere">
    <meta property="og:description" content="Install Very Good AdBlock for Chrome, Firefox, or Safari on Mac, iPhone, and iPad. No account, telemetry, or bloat.">
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://verygoodadblock.org/icons/icon-128.png">
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary">
    <meta name="twitter:title" content="Very Good AdBlock — fast, private ad blocking everywhere">
    <meta name="twitter:description" content="Available for Chrome, Firefox, and Safari on Mac, iPhone, and iPad. No telemetry.">
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://verygoodadblock.org/icons/icon-128.png">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="48x48" href="/icons/icon-48.png">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/icons/icon.svg">
    <title>Very Good AdBlock — fast, private ad blocker for Chrome, Firefox &amp; Safari</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
  </head>
  <body class="marketing-shell">
    @include('nav')

    <main id="top">
      <section class="marketing-hero">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Chrome · Firefox · Safari for Mac, iPhone &amp; iPad</p>
          <h1>Ads gone before the page loads.</h1>
          <p class="hero-lede">
            Very Good AdBlock removes ads, pop-ups, and YouTube and Twitch interruptions at the source,
            then stays out of the way. No telemetry, no bloat.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="primary-link" href="#get" data-browser-install>Choose your browser</a>
            <a class="download-pill" href="https://addons.mozilla.org/firefox/addon/very-good-adblock/" aria-label="Install Very Good AdBlock for Firefox">
              <img class="download-logo" src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/firefoxbrowser" alt="" width="20" height="20" loading="lazy">
              <span>Firefox</span>
            </a>
            <a class="download-pill" href="https://apps.apple.com/app/id6792576349" aria-label="Download Very Good AdBlock for Safari on Mac, iPhone, and iPad">
              <img class="download-logo" src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/safari" alt="" width="20" height="20" loading="lazy">
              <span>Safari</span>
            </a>
            <a class="download-pill" href="https://github.com/chrisbbreuer/very-good-adblock/releases/latest" aria-label="Download signed release packages from GitHub">
              <img class="download-logo" src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/github" alt="" width="20" height="20" loading="lazy">
              <span>Manual download</span>
            </a>
          </div>
          <a class="hero-how" href="#how">How it works →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-visual">
          <!-- The real popup component, inlined at build time from
               resources/partials/popup-preview.html (generated off the shipping popup). -->
          <div class="hero-device" id="popup-preview" role="img" aria-label="The Very Good AdBlock toolbar popup: 47 ads blocked on this page, 8.4 GB of data saved, 20 hours of video time recovered, and a chart of the last 24 hours."></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="features" class="marketing-band">
        <div class="section-kicker">
          <h2>Protection at the source, not fragile page rewrites.</h2>
          <a class="section-link" href="/features/">All features →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-grid">
          <a class="feature-card" href="/features/network-blocking/">
            <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 3 4 6v5c0 4.4 3.1 8.3 8 9.5 4.9-1.2 8-5.1 8-9.5V6l-8-3Z"></path><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <h3>Network blocking</h3>
            <p>Manifest V3 declarative rules stop 14,000+ ad, tracker, and annoyance hosts before the request completes.</p>
            <span class="feature-more">Learn more →</span>
          </a>
          <a class="feature-card" href="/features/youtube-twitch/">
            <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="3"></rect><path d="m10 9 5 3-5 3V9Z"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <h3>YouTube and Twitch</h3>
            <p>Strips video ads out of YouTube's player response, skips what slips through, and detects Twitch stream ads. The real video never breaks.</p>
            <span class="feature-more">Learn more →</span>
          </a>
          <a class="feature-card" href="/features/popups/">
            <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="2"></rect><path d="M3 9h18"></path><path d="m9.5 12.5 5 5M14.5 12.5l-5 5"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <h3>Pop-ups and pop-unders</h3>
            <p>Neutralizes the click-hijack pop-ups streaming and file-host sites open, including the ones fired from inside the player iframe.</p>
            <span class="feature-more">Learn more →</span>
          </a>
          <a class="feature-card" href="/features/controls/">
            <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 8h10M18 8h2M4 16h2M10 16h10"></path><circle cx="16" cy="8" r="2.4"></circle><circle cx="8" cy="16" r="2.4"></circle></svg>
            </span>
            <h3>Control and privacy</h3>
            <p>Pause per site, keep an allowlist, hide cookie banners, and read local stats from a clean dashboard. Nothing leaves your machine.</p>
            <span class="feature-more">Learn more →</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      @include('browsers-band')

      <section id="how" class="how-band">
        <h2>Running in about a minute.</h2>
        <ol class="how-steps">
          <li>
            <span class="how-num">1</span>
            <h3>Install</h3>
            <p>Use the Chrome Web Store, Firefox Add-ons, or the App Store for Safari on Mac, iPhone, and iPad.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="how-num">2</span>
            <h3>Enable it</h3>
            <p>Pin the browser button, or enable the Safari extension once in Settings on your Apple device.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="how-num">3</span>
            <h3>Browse</h3>
            <p>Ads, pop-ups, and video interruptions are gone before the page can render them.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section id="stats" class="stats-showcase">
        <div>
          <h2>Local stats make the blocking visible.</h2>
          <p>
            Lifetime blocks, a daily history, estimated bandwidth saved, and estimated video minutes recovered.
            Compact totals sync across your installs; the detailed history stays on the device.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-wall" aria-label="Very Good AdBlock stats examples">
          <article>
            <strong>52,910</strong>
            <span>lifetime blocks</span>
          </article>
          <article>
            <strong>8.4 GB</strong>
            <span>estimated data saved</span>
          </article>
          <article>
            <strong>19.6 hr</strong>
            <span>estimated video time saved</span>
          </article>
          <article>
            <strong>0</strong>
            <span>remote telemetry events</span>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="privacy" class="privacy-band">
        <div class="privacy-copy">
          <h2>No hidden telemetry. No remote rule surprises.</h2>
          <p>
            Rules ship with each release and refresh daily from a public list built from pinned filter revisions. Your site choices become local rules,
            and the dashboard marks every estimate as an estimate. Nothing about your browsing is sent anywhere.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="privacy-list">
          <div><span></span>Chrome MV3 declarativeNetRequest</div>
          <div><span></span>Site-specific cosmetic hiding, kill switch included</div>
          <div><span></span>Local and sync storage split</div>
          <div><span></span>Exportable stats and reset controls</div>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="cta-band">
        <div class="cta-inner">
          <span class="cta-badge">Free and open source</span>
          <h2>Browse like the ads were never there.</h2>
          <p>MIT licensed, built for Chrome, Firefox, macOS, iPhone, and iPad from one codebase, with no account and no telemetry.</p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="primary-link" href="#get" data-browser-install>Choose your browser</a>
            <a class="secondary-link" href="https://github.com/chrisbbreuer/very-good-adblock" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View source</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      @include('subscribe')
    </main>

    @include('footer')
    <script type="module" src="/marketing.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
